      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "What’s the difference between right and wrong? (Not merely ethically, but circumstancially.)",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "It’s obvious: Right is justified, wrong isn’t.",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Except what about when it isn’t so clear cut? When ‘wrong’",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "is",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "justifiable.",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "What do we do when the reasoning isn’t so cut and dry?",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "It’s certainly ’wrong’ to steal from a vending machine…but what about if you’re literally dying of thirst?",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "It’s clearly ‘wrong’ to be late for work…but what if it was caused by uncontrollable cirmstances (traffic accidents, snow storms, 300-story gorillas?)",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Or consider contrarians (of all kinds)? How do you know when it’s",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "foul-play",
          "marks": [
            "link-0"
          ]
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "versus the next clever invention? Or the next",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "clause",
          "marks": [
            "link-1"
          ]
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "you didn’t even know to expect?",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "A simple (and effective) solution might be to acknowledge that each case",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "is",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "different. Choosing to address problems on a case-by-case basis, instead of writing off a person or a situation because they apparently conform to a standard we’ve seen before.",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Because as it turns out, most cases are, in fact, the specific ones. One’s where simple principles and pithy aphorisms don’t apply.",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "The",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "trick",
          "marks": [
            "link-2"
          ]
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "is figuring out where these instances land on a sliding scale. Is it more like this, or more like that? Is it less or more tolerable than what we imagined?",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Certainly, there are no easy answers. That’s (sorta) the point.",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Because complex problems aren’t solved with simple solutions. They’re solved with a subtleness that bends (without breaking) the rules.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ],
